      "flags": {},
      "order": 0,
      "mode": 0,
      "properties": {"text": ""},
      "widgets_values": [
        "ATLAS SKY DOME — separate the sky, clean-plate it, project onto a flat far card (the standard DMP move, same idea as Nuke)\n\nWhy: monocular depth is unreliable/noisy on sky (see CLAUDE.md's 'Sky-aware depth'), and a real relief mesh has no reason to reconstruct sky as actual 3D geometry — it has essentially no parallax at any normal camera distance. AtlasSkyDomeLayer instead builds a flat, constant-depth card (radius_m) covering only the pixels a real segmentation marks as sky, UV-baked the same way every other relief mesh here is, so a clean sky plate projects onto it correctly and never tears or fights the ground geometry's own depth.\n\nTHIS GRAPH USES PLACEHOLDERS so it stays valid/runnable without extra installs (same convention as atlas_camera_inpaint_layers_workflow.json):\n- SolidMask (value=1, marks the WHOLE frame as 'sky') stands in for a real segmentation. Replace it with ComfyUI-RMBG's SAM3 Segmentation node prompted 'sky' (github.com/1038lab/ComfyUI-RMBG) — wire its MASK output into AtlasSkyDomeLayer's sky_mask input.\n- AtlasSkyDomeLayer's plate_image is wired directly to the original photo (not actually clean-plated yet). For a real clean sky plate: invert the SAM3 mask (its own invert_output widget, or a core InvertMask node) -> INPAINT_ExpandMask (grow ~16-32) -> INPAINT_InpaintWithModel (image=original photo, inpaint_model=big-lama.pt via INPAINT_LoadInpaintModel) -> wire that result into plate_image instead. See INSTALL.md's 'Optional Inpaint Integration'.\n\nradius_m (default 300) should comfortably exceed AtlasDeriveReliefMesh's own derived backdrop/scene-depth (see the viewport's Info HUD) so the sky card never intersects real geometry.\n\nOpen the Atlas Viewport, hit Project, then orbit — ground geometry and the sky card should composite seamlessly from Camera View, and unlike a depth-reconstructed sky, the card never tears on orbit since it's flat and constant-depth by construction. hole_mask (previewed bottom-right) is a QA signal only — it tracks sky_mask's own boundary, not something to feed back into inpainting.\n\nSee CLAUDE.md's 'Inpaint layers' key design rule and relief_mesh.build_sky_dome_mesh's docstring for the full rationale."
      ]
    },
